$interpreted: Dagger: We're hitting the left wing of the Sunshine Infantry's camp. We split into two forces. Thickpaw is in charge of the main force
Dagger: First, we do a frontal assault to lure out the human army.
Furygrowl: Lure out the human army?
Dagger: Yes, I'll take charge of the other force. Once the main force has lured out most of the humans from their camp
Furygrowl: I see, but there are two legions in the left wing. We'd have to make sure both legions leave their posts before attacking.
Furygrowl: Otherwise, the humans would get the upper hand.
Dagger: Don't worry, everything will be fine!
Dagger: Thickpaw's main forces are about to attack, let's move out!
Furygrowl: Dagger, wait, the second legion of the Sunshine Infantry hasn't moved yet!
Dagger: Wait any longer and Thickpaw gets all the glory, move out folks!
Dagger: Wha....m-more... human soldiers...!? I can't... keep up...
Teenage Bear: Out of options. Our main force has been pushed back... we have to retreat.
Dagger: No, Furygrowl is still out there. I'm not leaving without him!
